args: Renelle is regaling Vida with\ntales of past adventures.
...And then the stone gate shut, and I was\ntrapped in the ruins!
Cursing my luck, I frantically surveyed my\nsurroundings—and on the other side of the\nroom, I saw this mysterious figure.
Dangit, Nefaria! Don't scare me like that!
Apologies. You appeared rapt,\nand I yenned to know the cause.
I fear I have disturbed your gaiety.\nI shall take my leave.
Hold on! Now that you're here, we might\nas well listen to Renelle's story together.
She was just telling me about one of\nher most harrowing adventures.

That's right! She travels all over the world
to explore ruins and discover legendary
treasures. Along the way, there's always
traps, thrills, chills, and spills!
And on this particular adventure,\nI brought in probably the second-\nbiggest haul of my career. Heh!

It was an ancient ruin, long-buried in the
sandseas to the south. The traps were
ingenious—and deadly—but the treasures
inside were worth every bead of sweat.
I don't want to brag, but this is probably\nthe greatest story ever told. Ha ha!
I would fain enjoy listening to your\nrousing tales of derring-do.
Er...right then! C'mon, grab a seat!
So where was I... Ah! Right...
I was trapped within the ruin, and a\nmysterious figure was closing in.
Was it a person? An animal? A GHOST?\nNo, it was actually...
A towering stone statue equipped\nwith a razor-sharp spear!
What?! How was a statue moving?!
Anyways, I'm sure you took care of\nit lickety-split, right?
You bet! See, I figured out its secret\nthe moment I saw it. It turns out...
It sensed a foreign source of mana and\nsought to see it slain, yes?
I-I mean, yeah, you got it! Pretty sharp.

So, I channeled mana into the tools
I'd brought with me and scattered them
all around—and that TOTALLY confused
the statue.
It stopped dead in its tracks, leaving me\nfree to explore even deeper.

Woooow... You're amazing! I can't believe
you figured out how that statue worked
so quickly—and even thought up such
a perfect solution!
Heh, it was nothing, really. Just another\nday in the life!
And Nefaria, you figured out the trick\njust as fast—and you didn't even SEE\nthe statue!
Your extolment is misguided.\nThose ruins were—
AAANYWAY, I continued on, deeper into\nthe depths.
There were more traps, a big\nlong hallway, and a hidden door.\nAnd beyond that door was—
According to an antiquities dealer,\nthe snow crystal was—
A diplomatic gift given to commemorate\ntrade relations with the north.
As I drew closer to the treasure chest,\nI felt something eerie and dangerous\nin the air and—

You had only to avoid stepping
on the crest secluded in the floor,
and then you wouldn't have been
shot by the arrows.
I had made it to the deepest depths of the\nruin, and I took the final treasure in hand.\nIt was—
How do you know all these things?!
You know the traps, the treasures, and\neven the appraisal I got from the dang\nantiquities expert!
As it happens, I am intimately familiar\nwith the ruins you speak of.
But HOW?! Nobody had ever been\nthat deep before!
I heard Nefaria was the queen of an\nancient land.
If that's really true, then the ruins you\nwere in could have actually been...
Score one for Vida! So the rumors\nare true then? You're the queen of\nlegend?
I think I owe you an apology, Nefaria.

I hunt treasure because whoever owned
it bit the dust a long time ago; it's not
doing them any good. But stealing from
the living? That just makes me a thief.
And I've got way too much pride for that.\nSo here's a promise...
I'll buy back every last piece of treasure\nI stole from you and return them all.

As you explained, those trinkets served
no purpose imprisoned in the sands.
They are for the better, returned to
the world.
Save your intervention, they would be\nmouldering in darkness still—so I\nadjudge your actions good.
Should you swell your purse with them,\nor delight Vida with tales of their\nprocurement, then all the better.
Wow—not just a queen,\nbut a GENEROUS queen.
Y-you're really giving me the okay to\nkeep looting your old home?
Well, I hope you know I don't do any\njob halfway!
Word on the street is there are plenty\nof buried ruins left to find.
So you better believe I'm gonna dig\nup each one, find all the treasures,\nand sell 'em to the highest bidder!
If you don't want me dredging up your\ngrandpa's favorite chamberpot or whatever,\nthis is your last chance to back out!
Such things are long swept from\nmy memory.
So in truth, you would do me a great\nkindness by unearthing them.

My subjects who built those ruins would
surely be pleased for them to see the
light of day once more, and it will
honor their memory besides.
I await your expedition\nwith alacrity, Renelle.
Sure, keep up the calm act while you can.\nThe next time we meet, I'm gonna surprise\nyou so hard you'll—
Say, Nefaria? Are there any knives\nin your ruins?
Well then I'm comin' too. Ancient ruins\nplus knives equals LEGENDARY KNIVES!
I recall not their annals,\nbut I pray you find joy.
We totally will! All right, all that's left now\nis to let Renelle find those ruins for us!
Indeed. I leave this in your hands,\nRenelle.
DON'T I GET A SAY IN THIS?!
